HEADWORD: Liss
<hw>Liss</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>lissan</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To free, as from care or pain; to relieve.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Lissed</xex> of his care.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

